# Commit Message Format (Conventional Commits)

Applies to **new commits from now on**. Do not rewrite already-pushed history to retitle old commits.

## Header (required shape)

**One line only** for the commit title:

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>
```

| Field | Required | Notes |
|-------|----------|-------|
| `type` | yes | What kind of change (see table below) |
| `scope` | no | Where in the repo; omit when change spans many areas equally |
| `subject` | yes | Imperative summary; English; no trailing period |

**Examples**

```
feat(web): scroll to top on every route change
fix(web): align Immersive info icon with WPM tooltip
docs(state): ADR-0014 §12 and STATE for route scroll
docs(adr): accept ADR-0015 session timer pause rules
chore(web): add scroll navigation probe script
```

## Types (use one)

| Type | Use when |
|------|----------|
| `feat` | User-visible capability or meaningful UX behavior |
| `fix` | Bug fix or regression |
| `docs` | `docs/STATE.md`, `docs/DECISIONS.md`, `docs/STATS.md`, or `.cursor/rules` only |
| `refactor` | Internal restructure; no intended behavior change |
| `test` | Tests or probe scripts whose main purpose is verification |
| `chore` | Tooling, deps, CI, formatting; no product behavior change |

**Don't** invent rare types (`style`, `perf`, …) unless the owner asks — pick the closest row above.

## Scopes (EchoType)

| Scope | Typical paths |
|-------|----------------|
| `web` | `apps/web/` |
| `api` | `apps/api/` |
| `shared` | `packages/shared/` |
| `state` | `docs/STATE.md` (often with `docs` type) |
| `adr` | `docs/DECISIONS.md` (often with `docs` type) |
| `stats` | `docs/STATS.md` (often with `docs` type) |
| `rules` | `.cursor/rules/` |
| `deploy` | `deploy/`, `.github/workflows/` |

Omit scope when a single commit fairly touches web + api + shared (rare); say so in the body if needed.

## Subject rules

**Do**

- Imperative mood: `add`, `fix`, `remove`, `align` — not `added` / `fixes`
- Lowercase first letter after the colon (proper nouns OK: `EchoType`, `WPM`, `ADR-0014`)
- ~72 characters or fewer when practical
- Focus on **what** changed; put **why** in the body

**Don't**

- End the subject with `.`
- Use `Phase N` alone as the subject — put phase context in the body if helpful
- Write Chinese in the header (`language-policy.mdc`)

## Body and footers (optional)

- Blank line after header, then body paragraphs are fine
- Body: why the change matters (aligns with `git-commit-push.mdc`)
- No `Co-authored-by` (`no-co-authored-by.mdc`)

## Two-commit discipline

When shipping a phased capability (`state-decisions-maintenance.mdc`):

1. **Work commit** — `feat(web): …`, `fix(api): …`, etc.
2. **Docs commit** — `docs(state): …` and/or `docs(adr): …` / `docs(stats): …` in a **separate** commit after the anchor sha exists

**Don't** drop Conventional Commits for phase work; use type/scope in the header and phase detail in the body.

## Agent workflow

When drafting a commit message for user review, **always** show the full header in `type(scope): subject` form. If the change does not fit any type/scope cleanly, say so and propose the closest match before committing.
